{#
===============================================================================
CENTRALIZED NOTIFICATION MESSAGES
File: /config/templates/notifications.jinja
Purpose: Single source of truth for all notification message templates
Updated: 2025-10-28
===============================================================================

This file contains all notification message templates used across your
Home Assistant automations. Messages are defined as Jinja2 macros that can
be called from any automation with dynamic parameters.

USAGE IN AUTOMATIONS:
  {% from 'notifications.jinja' import message_name %}
  {{ message_name(param1='value1', param2='value2') }}

TELEGRAM vs EMAIL:
  - Each message type has two versions: _telegram and _email
  - Telegram uses markdown formatting (* for bold, etc.)
  - Email uses plain text with separators or HTML formatting

PARAMETER NAMING:
  - device_name: Name of the device triggering the alert
  - battery_level: Current battery percentage
  - threshold: Battery threshold value
  - alert_count: Number of alerts
  - timestamp: Date/time of the alert
  - And more specific to each message type
#}

