{#
TO ADD NEW MESSAGES:
1. Create two macros: one for Telegram (_telegram) and one for Email (_email)
2. Define parameters clearly in the comment block above each macro
3. Use Jinja2 syntax for dynamic content: {{ variable_name }}
4. Use filters for formatting: | round(2), | default('Unknown'), etc.
5. Telegram uses markdown: * for bold, • for bullets
6. Email uses plain text with separators: ==== and ----
7. Test the macro before deploying to production

EXAMPLE USAGE IN AUTOMATION:
  - service: telegram_bot.send_message
    data:
      config_entry_id: 01K7PH2MD1SA9VXHCP39WVCJM4
      message: >
        {% from 'notifications.jinja' import low_battery_alert_telegram %}
        {{ low_battery_alert_telegram(
             device_name=repeat.item.name | replace(' Battery', ''),
             battery_level=repeat.item.battery,
             threshold=states('input_number.battery_low_threshold') | float,
             timestamp=now()
        ) }}
      parse_mode: markdown
#}